title: incremental compilation error with explicit_predicates_of, item_children

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
This error is related to #84970. This error is caused by running cargo check or cargo doc with an incremental cache. I believe the cache is from a previous rust version. (Currently using 1.55.0) Cargo build works fine. ### Code I don't believe I can create a minimal verifiable example because this bug relies on the incremental cache. Changing anything causes recompilation and avoids the error. I can provide all code and target directory if necessary. ### Meta Switching to nightly causes recompilation and avoids the error. `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.55.0 (c8dfcfe04 2021-09-06) binary: rustc commit-hash: c8dfcfe046a7680554bf4eb612bad840e7631c4b commit-date: 2021-09-06 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.55.0 LLVM version: 12.0.1 ``` ### Error output This is one instance of the error. The same error happens on multiple crates in the project. ``` error: internal compiler error: encountered incremental compilation error with explicit_predicates_of(nox_util[8b2e]::serde::DeserializeFallible) | = help: This is a known issue with the compiler. Run `cargo clean -p nox_pak` or `cargo clean` to allow your project to compile = note: Please follow the instructions below to create a bug report with the provided information = note: See for more information error: internal compiler error: encountered incremental compilation error with item_children(nox_util[8b2e]) | = help: This is a known issue with the compiler.
